{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, ethical considerations surrounding AI-driven sensory manipulation, especially in consumer-facing applications, remain underexplored.",
    "Issues related to data privacy, transparency in sensory personalization, informed consumer consent, and accountability require thorough ethical scrutiny and clear policy guidelines (Adekugbe and Ibeh 2024).",
    "Carefully navigating these ethical challenges is essential to ensuring responsible, trustworthy, and societally acceptable AI implementations in olfactory and gustatory applications.",
    "In addition, while existing studies have extensively mapped AI's role in odor and taste analysis, several critical gaps remain.",
    "Most AI models treat olfaction and gustation as isolated modalities, neglecting their synergistic effects in flavor perception."
  ]
}